3":"1248–1333","1275–Male":"1275–Overleden","1276–1303":"1276–1303","1288–1385":"1288–1385","1310–Male":"1310–Overleden","1223–1282":"1223–1282","1225–Female":"1225–Overleden","1385":"1385","1275":"1275","1282":"1282","1303":"1303","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1333":"1333","1278":"1278","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1276":"1276","1254":"1254","about 1275":"circa 1275","about 1254":"circa 1254","1329":"1329","Ongar, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Ongar, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Ongar Park, Essex, England":"Essex, England","Willingale, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Willingale, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Ongar Park,Essex,England":"Ongar, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1254–":"about 1254–Deceased","1254–Female":"1254–Deceased","1278–1329":"1278–1329","1248–1333":"1248–1333","1275–Male":"1275–Deceased","1276–1303":"1276–1303","1288–1385":"1288–1385","1310–Male":"1310–Deceased","1223–1282":"1223–1282","1225–Female":"1225–Deceased","1385":"1385","1275":"1275","1282":"1282","1303":"1303","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1333":"1333","1278":"1278","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1276":"1276","1254":"1254","about 1275":"about 1275","about 1254":"about 1254","1329":"1329","Ongar, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Ongar, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Ongar Park, Essex, England":"Essex, England","Willingale, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Willingale, Essex, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ongar Park,Essex,England":"Ongar, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Torrell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: (i) nickname from Old French  <i>torel</i> ‘young bull’.  See also  Torr  . Some of the bearers below may belong under (2). (ii) variant of   Turrell  .","2  English: locative name for someone who lived or worked at a lime kiln or a malt kiln (Middle English  <i>torel</i>, Old French  <i>toraile</i> ‘little tower, kiln’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Tyrrell","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): perhaps a nickname from a derivative of Old French <i>tirer</i> ‘to pull’, in the same sense as French <i>Tirand</i> ‘one who pulls on the reins’, hence ‘obstinate, stubborn’. This name may have become confused with   Turrell  . A branch of this Anglo-Norman family has been in Ireland since the 12th century. Its name has been Gaelicized as <b>Tirial</b>.","English: habitational name from Tirril (Cumbria), which derives from Old Norse <i>tyri</i> ‘resinous wood’ + <i>erg</i> ‘shieling’."]},{"name":"Thorold","meanings":["English: relationship name from the Anglo-Norman and Middle English personal name  <i>T(h)urold</i>,  <i>T(h)orold</i>,  <i>T(h)orald</i> (Old Scandinavian  <i>Þóraldr</i>). The initial  <i>T</i> is due to the Anglo-Norman pronunciation of  <i>Th-</i>.  <i>Torald</i> and  <i>Torold</i> became  <i>Toraud</i> and  <i>Toroud</i>, giving the modern surname  <i>Torode</i>. This name may have become confused with   Tyrrell  ,   Turrill  , and   Torrell  ."]},{"name":"Turrell","meanings":["English (southeastern and East Anglia):","most frequently an Anglo-Norman French pronunciation of <i>Thorold</i> (Old Norse <i>Thóraldr</i>, from the elements <i>Thórr</i> ‘Thor’ + <i>valdr</i> ‘power, rule’). This name and that in 2 may have become confused with   Tyrrell  .","from Middle English <i>T(h)urild</i> (Old Norse <i>Thórhildr</i>, <i>Thorild</i>, the latter a rare woman's name from the divine name <i>Thórr</i> ‘Thor’ + <i>hildr</i> ‘battle’)."]},{"name":"Torr","meanings":["English:","from Middle English <i>tor(re)</i> ‘rocky peak, hill’ (Old English <i>torr</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived on or by a hill, or toponymic, from a place so named, such as <i>Torre</i>, the earlier name of Torquay (Devon). The element is especially common in placenames in southwestern England, particularly Devon, but it is occasionally found in other English regions, such as Sussex and Derbyshire.","nickname for someone thought to resemble a bull, from Old French <i>tor</i> (from Latin <i>taurus</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Christina","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Simplified form of Latin <i>Christiana</i>, feminine form of <i>Christianus</i> (  see  Christian  ), or a Latinized form of Middle English <i>Christin</i> ‘Christian’ (Old English <i>christen</i>, from Latin)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Christina Torrell was born about 1254, in Willingale, Essex, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Torrell, was 33 and her mother, Agnes, was 31. She had at least 5 sons with Sir Geoffrey Battell."},"et":{"about 1254–":"umbes 1254–Surnud","1254–Female":"1254–Surnud","1278–1329":"1278–1329","1248–1333":"1248–1333","1275–Male":"1275–Surnud","1276–1303":"1276–1303","1288–1385":"1288–1385","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1223–1282":"1223–1282","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1385":"1385","1275":"1275","1282":"1282","1303":"1303","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1333":"1333","1278":"1278","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1276":"1276","1254":"1254","about 1275":"umbes 1275","about 1254":"umbes 1254","1329":"1329","Ongar, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Ongar, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ongar Park, Essex, England":"Essex, England","Willingale, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Willingale, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ongar Park,Essex,England":"Ongar, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1254–":"noin 1254–Kuollut","1254–Female":"1254–Kuollut","1278–1329":"1278–1329","1248–1333":"1248–1333","1275–Male":"1275–Kuollut","1276–1303":"1276–1303","1288–1385":"1288–1385","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1223–1282":"1223–1282","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1385":"1385","1275":"1275","1282":"1282","1303":"1303","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1223":"122